Interface IApplicantService

All Known Subinterfaces:
IOfficerService
All Known Implementing Classes:
ApplicantService, OfficerService
public interface IApplicantService
Interface for services related to an HDB applicant. Provides methods for project applications, enquiries, and application management.

  • Method Details

    • haveProject

      boolean haveProject()
      Checks if the applicant has already applied for a project.
      Returns:
      true if the applicant has a project, false otherwise

    • getVisibleProjects

      List<Project> getVisibleProjects()
      Retrieves a list of currently visible and eligible projects for the applicant.
      Returns:
      a list of visible and eligible Project objects

    • isEligibleForProject

      boolean isEligibleForProject(Project project)
      Determines if the applicant is eligible to apply for the specified project.
      Parameters:
      project - the project to check eligibility for
      Returns:
      true if eligible, false otherwise

    • isSingle

      boolean isSingle()
      Checks if the applicant is single.
      Returns:
      true if the applicant is single, false otherwise

    • newApplication

      Application newApplication(Project project, int flatType)
      Creates a new application for the specified project and flat type.
      Parameters:
      project - the project to apply for
      flatType - the type of flat (1 for 2-Room, 2 for 3-Room)
      Returns:
      the created Application object

    • sendApplication

      void sendApplication(Application application)
      Submits the given application and updates the applicant's status.
      Parameters:
      application - the Application to be submitted

    • getProject

      Project getProject()
      Retrieves the project the applicant has applied for.
      Returns:
      the Project the applicant is currently assigned to, or null if none

    • isAvailableToBookFlat

      boolean isAvailableToBookFlat()
      Checks if the applicant is eligible to book a flat. Eligibility requires a successful application.
      Returns:
      true if eligible to book a flat, false otherwise

    • withdrawalApplication

      void withdrawalApplication()
      Submits a withdrawal request for the applicant's current application.

    • submitEnquiry

      void submitEnquiry(String q, Project project)
      Submits an enquiry about a specific project.
      Parameters:
      q - the enquiry message
      project - the project the enquiry is related to

    • getEnquiries

      List<Enquiry> getEnquiries()
      Retrieves all enquiries submitted by the applicant.
      Returns:
      a list of Enquiry objects

    • getEnquiry

      Enquiry getEnquiry(int enquiryId)
      Retrieves a specific enquiry by its ID.
      Parameters:
      enquiryId - the ID of the enquiry
      Returns:
      the Enquiry object if found, or null if not found

    • editEnquiry

      void editEnquiry(String q, Enquiry enquiry)
